Rating: 3
This is an incredibly fast and satisfying meal. I found that the flavor of the pesto is crucial to this simple dish. I made some of my own pesto with basil from the garden (see easy recipe below) to terrific results. My only critical comment is that with sufficiently delicious pesto the extra kick of flavor from the bacon is unnecessary. It actually made the dish a bit too heavy for me. My boyfriend however thought the bacon was a delicious addition. In short, if you're using store- bought pesto I'd stick with the bacon but maybe use a bit less. I recommend this satisfying, quick recipe; especially if you're trying new ways to use abundant garden zucchini! Pesto: mix together in a blender until smooth: 2 cups fresh basil leaves, 3/4 c. parm cheese grated, 3/4 c. olive oil, 3 garlic cloves, 1/4 c. pine nuts. If you're low on basil leaves try substituting the last 1/2 c. with chopped zucchini and a large pinch of oregano leaves.

