Rating: 4
Mmmmmm, very delicious and a big hit with my family. However, I did not like the idea of boiling the vegetables, especially the zucchini. It just did not seem the best way to bring out their flavor and might make the zucchini soggy and tasteless. Grilling is an excellent idea but it was pouring rain here so instead, using a 5 qt sauté pan, I poured off most of the grease from the bacon and simply stir-fried the chopped zucchini and the corn on high heat for not more than 1 or 2 minutes, leaving the zucchini crisp-tender. Then I added the pasta, bacon, and the pesto (Deb Madison's recipe from her vegetarian cookbook). The pesto was made with all Thai basil and that worked very well. I used Raven, Kousa and Sultan zucchinis from our garden and I let them sit for awhile (chopped) on a clean cotton towel to remove some of the excess moisture. These all have tender skin that can be left on if organic, adding additional color to the dish. I think very thick-sliced bacon also works best with this recipe. How wonderful it is to enter what I've picked from the garden that day into the Epicurious database and find wonderful recipes like this one!

